### MERN AI Flow Backend - API Testing
### Use with REST Client extension in VS Code or any HTTP client

### Base URL - Change this based on your environment
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000
@apiUrl = {{baseUrl}}/api/ai

### ============================================
### 1. HEALTH CHECK
### ============================================

### Test server health
GET {{baseUrl}}/
Content-Type: application/json

### Expected Response:
# {
#   "status": "OK",
#   "timestamp": "2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z"
# }

### ============================================
### 2. AI GENERATION TESTS
### ============================================

### Test 1: Generate AI response with basic prompt
POST {{apiUrl}}/generate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "What is the capital of France?"
}

### Test 2: Generate AI response with longer prompt
POST {{apiUrl}}/generate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "Explain quantum computing in simple terms for a 10-year-old."
}

### Test 3: Generate AI response with custom model (Mistral)
POST {{apiUrl}}/generate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "Write a short poem about programming in JavaScript",
  "model": "openrouter/auto"
}

### Test 4: Generate AI response with Gemini model (default)
POST {{apiUrl}}/generate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "What are the top 3 programming languages for beginners and why?",
  "model": "openrouter/auto"
}

### Test 5: Generate AI response with creative task
POST {{apiUrl}}/generate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "Create a fun 5-question quiz about space exploration with answers."
}

### Test 6: Test error case - empty prompt
POST {{apiUrl}}/generate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": ""
}

### Test 7: Test error case - missing prompt
POST {{apiUrl}}/generate
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### ============================================
### 3. SAVE CONVERSATION TESTS
### ============================================

### Test 1: Save a complete conversation
POST {{apiUrl}}/save
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "What is the capital of France?",
  "response": "The capital of France is Paris.",
  "modelUsed": "openrouter/auto"
}

### Test 2: Save another conversation
POST {{apiUrl}}/save
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "What is 2+2?",
  "response": "2 + 2 equals 4.",
  "modelUsed": "openrouter/auto",
  "metadata": {
    "topic": "math",
    "difficulty": "easy"
  }
}

### Test 3: Save conversation about programming
POST {{apiUrl}}/save
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "What is React?",
  "response": "React is a JavaScript library for building user interfaces, developed by Facebook.",
  "modelUsed": "mistralai/mistral-7b-instruct:free"
}

### Test 4: Save creative conversation
POST {{apiUrl}}/save
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "Write a joke about programming",
  "response": "Why do programmers prefer dark mode? Because light attracts bugs!",
  "modelUsed": "google/gemini-2.0-flash-lite-preview-02-05:free"
}

### Test 5: Save conversation with metadata
POST {{apiUrl}}/save
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "What's the weather like today?",
  "response": "I don't have access to real-time weather data, but you can check a weather service!",
  "modelUsed": "google/gemini-2.0-flash-lite-preview-02-05:free",
  "metadata": {
    "timestamp": "2024-01-01T12:00:00Z",
    "user": "test-user-1",
    "category": "weather"
  }
}

### Test 6: Save error case - missing prompt
POST {{apiUrl}}/save
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "response": "This is a response without a prompt"
}

### Test 7: Save error case - missing response
POST {{apiUrl}}/save
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "This is a prompt without response"
}

### ============================================
### 4. GET CONVERSATIONS TESTS
### ============================================

### Test 1: Get all conversations (should return latest 50)
GET {{apiUrl}}/conversations
Content-Type: application/json

### Test 2: Get conversations with limit (using query params if supported)
GET {{apiUrl}}/conversations?limit=10
Content-Type: application/json

### ============================================
### 5. GET SINGLE CONVERSATION TESTS
### ============================================

### First, get all conversations to find an ID
GET {{apiUrl}}/conversations

### Then use the ID from above response to test single conversation
# @prompt conversationId REPLACE_WITH_ACTUAL_ID_FROM_ABOVE

### Test 1: Get conversation by ID (replace with actual ID)
GET {{apiUrl}}/conversations/65f5a1b2c3d4e5f6a7b8c9d0
Content-Type: application/json

### Test 2: Get conversation with invalid ID
GET {{apiUrl}}/conversations/invalid-id-123
Content-Type: application/json

### ============================================
### 6. COMPLETE WORKFLOW TESTS
### ============================================

### Workflow 1: Generate, then Save
### Step 1: Generate AI response
POST {{apiUrl}}/generate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "What are the benefits of meditation?"
}

### Step 2: Save the generated response (copy response from above)
POST {{apiUrl}}/save
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "What are the benefits of meditation?",
  "response": "Meditation offers numerous benefits including reduced stress, improved focus, better emotional health, and enhanced self-awareness.",
  "modelUsed": "google/gemini-2.0-flash-lite-preview-02-05:free"
}

### Workflow 2: Full flow with metadata
### Step 1: Generate creative response
POST {{apiUrl}}/generate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "Create a short story about a robot learning to paint"
}

### Step 2: Save with metadata
POST {{apiUrl}}/save
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "Create a short story about a robot learning to paint",
  "response": "Once upon a time, a robot named Artie discovered colors...",
  "modelUsed": "google/gemini-2.0-flash-lite-preview-02-05:free",
  "metadata": {
    "genre": "sci-fi",
    "theme": "creativity",
    "wordCount": 150
  }
}

### ============================================
### 7. BULK OPERATIONS TEST
### ============================================

### Create multiple conversations quickly
POST {{apiUrl}}/save
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "What is machine learning?",
  "response": "Machine learning is a subset of AI that enables systems to learn from data.",
  "modelUsed": "google/gemini-2.0-flash-lite-preview-02-05:free"
}

###

POST {{apiUrl}}/save
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "What is TypeScript?",
  "response": "TypeScript is a typed superset of JavaScript that compiles to plain JavaScript.",
  "modelUsed": "google/gemini-2.0-flash-lite-preview-02-05:free"
}

###

POST {{apiUrl}}/save
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "What is MongoDB?",
  "response": "MongoDB is a NoSQL document database that stores data in flexible JSON-like documents.",
  "modelUsed": "google/gemini-2.0-flash-lite-preview-02-05:free"
}

### ============================================
### 8. ERROR HANDLING TESTS
### ============================================

### Test 1: Invalid route
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/invalid-route
Content-Type: application/json

### Test 2: Wrong HTTP method
POST {{apiUrl}}/conversations
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "test": "This should fail"
}

### Test 3: Malformed JSON
POST {{apiUrl}}/generate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "This has malformed JSON

### Test 4: Too large payload (if you want to test)
POST {{apiUrl}}/generate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "A".repeat(10000)
}

### ============================================
### 9. PERFORMANCE TESTS
### ============================================

### Test concurrent requests (run multiple times quickly)
### Request 1
POST {{apiUrl}}/generate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "What is Node.js?"
}

### Request 2 (run immediately after)
POST {{apiUrl}}/generate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "What is Express.js?"
}

### Request 3
POST {{apiUrl}}/generate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "What is React?"
}

### ============================================
### 10. ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES TEST
### ============================================

### Check if MongoDB is connected (should return conversations)
GET {{apiUrl}}/conversations
Content-Type: application/json

### This will show if database connection is working
# - If returns empty array: Database is connected but no data
# - If returns error: Database connection issue
# - If returns conversations: Everything working

